(790, 666, '_edit_last', '10'),
(791, 666, '_genesis_title', 'Who is Driving the Crowd?'),
(792, 666, '_genesis_description', 'Crowdfunding is all the rage in the first quarter of 2015, with many leading Venture Capital putting their money on the new industry they see as the future of finance; a democratized one at that. The industry is not new, however, as musicians in the 1980s commonly used its capital raising power to draw a living wage from fans and friends, hoping to make it to the big entertainment business leagues.'),
(793, 668, '_edit_lock', '1433268159:13'),
(794, 668, '_edit_last', '10'),
(795, 668, '_genesis_title', 'What is to Account for the Rise in Equity Crowdfunding?'),
(796, 668, '_genesis_description', 'Equity crowdfunding is still a foreign concept for many individuals. To understand why equity crowdfunding is emerging on a global level, we must first recognize the financing inefficiencies that hinder startups and investors alike.'),
(797, 669, '_edit_lock', '1433183876:13'),
(798, 669, '_edit_last', '4'),
(799, 669, '_genesis_title', 'We know equity crowdfunding, but what is "pre-crowd"?'),
(800, 669, '_genesis_description', 'Equity crowdfunding as an industry has grown from an annual $1.5 billion raised in 2011, to a predicted annual total of nearly $11 billion in 2015. What''s more studies by the World Bank Group predicts the industry''s expansion into an industry annually raising up to $96 billion, overall set rise to almost three-times the size of today''s venture capital industry. '),
(801, 672, '_edit_lock', '1429850791:10'),
