(705, 10, '2015-05-11 18:38:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'On July 10th, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oscar_Jofre">Oscar Jofre</a>, the celebrated and successful serial technology entrepreneur will address attendees of the <a href="https://www.latamstartups.biz/">LATAM Startup Conf 2.0</a>, at the MaRS Disc<img class=" size-full wp-image-718 alignright" src="http://koreconx.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/latam-startup-conference-logotype2.jpg" alt="latam-startup-conference-logotype2" width="440" height="160" />overy Center. The event promises to be informative and transformative given the 360 degrees perspective on investing and successfully launching a business in Latin America. Few investors in the country could be better positioned to address a crowd of practitioners as Oscar Jofre, given his status as a veteran of successful technology investing, government relations, and capital raising in both North and South America.\r\n\r\nOscar Jofre holds a noted track record of successful technology entrepreneurship in Canada. He heads one of the world’s best equity crowdfunding platforms, <a href="http://www.koreconx.com/">KoreConX</a>. Prior to this, he founded the <a href="http://canadait.ca/cfm/index.cfm?It=106&amp;Id=14925&amp;Se=2&amp;Lo=442">BabelFish Corporation</a> in 1999, a specialist multi-lingual translation platform. Having matured this first venture, he went on to create a leading, highly secure, application-collaborative platform called <a href="http://www.boardsuitecorp.com/about_executive_team.php">Boardsuite</a>. While the list is not exhaustive, it is clear that Jofre holds several decades of experience when it comes to having faced the challenges of starting, building, maturing, and advising startups throughout their commercial life-cycle.\r\n\r\nHis experience is not restricted to management prowess. Throughout the bulk of his career, Jofre has acquired a veritable arsenal of government relations and global governance acumen. As the Chair of the Canadian Network of Language Industries Network (CNLI), he collaborated with other noted industry players as part of a broader government mandate to bring Language Industries together federally.\r\n\r\nIn addition to this first effort at bridging the gap between business and government, Jofre assisted in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Industry_Canada">Industry Canada</a>, the government agency, and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Research_Council_of_Canada">National Research Council of Canada</a>, in their effort to map the emerging language industry, identify its principal stakeholders, assess the state of Canadian research in the field, and advise on the country’s international strategy to emerge as a global leader.\r\n\r\nInternationally, Oscar is a full member of the <a href="http://www.cfira.org/">Crowdfunding Intermediary Regulatory Advocates</a> group in the United States, in charge of government relations to improve standards and rules applicable to service-providers involved in the crowdfunding sector. On our side of the border, he is the co-Chair of Canada’s national <a href="http://www.ecfacanada.ca/">Equity Crowdfunding Alliance</a>.\r\n\r\nOscar Jofre was the only Canadian among those at the helm of the joint United Nations and Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) Digital Nations Board, exercising this duty for nearly four years in a row. In this role, Jofre helped shape and coordinate the Board’s approach and strategy with regards to Esperanto, the language, and see to its expansion as the world’s widest spoken auxiliary language.\r\n\r\nAs a result of his consistent efforts for the past decades, Oscar Jofre is seen, and <a href="http://www.peterkent.ca/view/news/97">was officially acknowledged</a>, as one of the country’s 10 most influential Hispanic Canadians; a commendation that was personally marked by Canada’s Prime Minister, Stephen Harper, and past winners of the same award.\r\n\r\nJofre’s contribution during the LATAM Startups Conf 2.0 event will be highly anticipated.', 'Oscar Jofre Speaks at LATAM Conference', '', 'pending', 'open', 'closed', '', 'oscar-jofre-speaks-latam-conference', '', '', '2015-05-11 18:38:35', '2015-05-11 18:38:35', '', 0, 'http://koreconx.com/?p=705', 0, 'post', '', 0),
